  Purpose: central visual hub for all upgraded IDE builds.
- /workspaces/SkyeCDE/Skye0s-s0l26/Sky0s-Platforms/SkyeCDE/README.md
  Purpose: explain the SkyeCDE hub architecture.
- /workspaces/SkyeCDE/Skye0s-s0l26/Sky0s-Platforms/SkyeCDE/skyecde-manifest.json
  Purpose: declare upgraded IDE builds and routing metadata.

Routing rule

The SkyeCDE platform root should launch a real hub page.
That hub page should link users into the upgraded IDE builds as full app launches, not preview widgets.

Product boundary rule

SkyeCDE owns the upgraded IDE hub experience.
SkyDex, SuperIDE, SkaixuPro-IDE, and KaixuSuper-IDE still own their original products.
The upgraded builds are additive products under SkyeCDE, not replacements of the originals.

Acceptance criteria

SkyeCDE is done as a hub when:
- the platform root opens a real hub page
- the hub lists each upgraded IDE build
- users can launch each upgraded IDE from the hub cleanly
- the original platforms remain intact outside the hub

